ce research is how to capture the richness of people’s social and cultural engagement with film. To achieve this, the book uses an innovative mixed-methods research and computational ontology. It develops ground-breaking theory and concepts and an innovative methodology based on an extensive data-set derived from the under-researched area of British regional film audiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture audiences. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2022. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aaudience formation.  aaudience studies.  aaudience trends.  acomputational ontology.  afilm audiences.  afilm consumption.  afilm policy.  afilm provision.  afilm, specialised and mainstream.  amixed methods.1 aForrest, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanchard, Matthew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHanchard, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMerrington, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMerrington, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeam, the Beyond the Multiplex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWessels, Bridgette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez9783111281988oZDB-23-MUP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez9783111281445oZDB-23-MUP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615784340uhttps://www.deg